==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paris
<hw>Par"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Paris</etsep>, the son of Priam.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
plant common in Europe (<spn>Paris quadrifolia</spn>); herb Paris;
truelove. It has been used as a narcotic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It much resembles the American genus
<gen>Trillium</gen>, but has usually four leaves and a tetramerous
flower.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paris</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Paris
<hw>Par"is</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The chief city of France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Paris green</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Green</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></cd> -- <col><b>Paris white</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>purified chalk used as a pigment; whiting; Spanish
white.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>parish</ent>⟦br⟧
